laboratory_examinations.findings: Diverticulosis in the descending and sigmoid colons with focal thickening of the sigmoid colon and adjacent inflammatory changes. Early intramural abscess formation (measuring about 2.5 x 2 cm). No free air or fluid noted. Urinary bladder, uterus normal. A 1.9 cm likely functional cyst in the left ovary. Trace pelvic free fluid present.
